I've been coming here for about a year and the food is normally tasty, but sometimes you'll get food that's extremely dry, like it's been left out for a really long time. Few days ago I brought a Cobb salad and the chicken was EXTREMELY dry. Another time about half a year ago, the mac and cheese was so dried out that the pasta was glued together like a ball, tasted like water, and had no sauce. I usually come here during the later afternoon and on weekends, times when people don't have lunch hour, so might that be the problem? Because if the dry food I sometimes get from here was served at a lunch hour, you'd have so many customers angry and complaining, so maybe they get too comfortable outside of lunch hour to the point that they neglect the food

I’m a big fan of Fields Good Chicken. Very clean and tasty chicken options. During lunch it can be busy but the service is great, quick and it’s a nice healthy option. I typically order one of the bowls although the salads are nice too. The herb chicken is my favorite with Mojo and BBQ as the runners up. If you go around 2pm you won’t have to wait in a long line and there will be plenty of seats available.

I usually don't leave reviews but I somehow feel obligated to post one for FGC. I love this place! It's super healhty and they have generous quantity. The place is not finicky about subsituting ingredients and will gladly let you pick and choose your ingredients. They usually have a long line during lunch hours but the staff is quite well trained and the line moves fairly quickly. I get my lunch here almost 4times a week. I wish they had a loyalty program. But I can't really complaint. All in all it's one the best healthy options with generous serving size and very friendly staff.

I have ordered from here for a couple years now and love the food but something has changed because the last few orders have had sauces EXPLODED ALL OVER MY ORDER, items missing, the wrong order sent, or an extended wait time of an hour!!?? Im a 5 minute walk away from this location and it was still such a hassle for delivery. I then called and the male over the phone was rude enough to keep interrupting me after giving me insufficient excuses on why the order was wrong. I had to reorder and wait an additional 30 minutes before receiving the remainder of order which had sauce exploded everywhere. Now I get to microwave their already dry chicken? If I wanted that I would've cooked at home. If they fix these delivery and customer service issues they might not go out of business.

I got the 1/2 Chicken with a side of Sriracha sauce. It really doesn't need the sauce because the chicken was brined overnight and then slow roasted. This equates to moist goodness on my taste buds! I love new restaurants open in my neighborhood so I got more options! Fields Good Kitchen makes you feel good just by walking in! I love how they use organic chicken and all the ingredients are healthy (supposedly).  I had the kale salad with grilled chicken and it is really tasty and healthy. The con is it is pricier and smaller than regular tossed salad. But I guess being healthy is priceless!?!!? Will come back for other things on the menu.
